[src:inductive-sensing/inductance] Currents in the wires need not be equal, though they often are, as in the case of a complete circuit, where one wire is the source and the other the return.
[src:inductive-sensing/inductance] This is the generalized case of the paradigmatic two-loop cylindrical coil carrying a uniform low frequency current; the loops are independent closed circuits that can have different lengths, any orientation in space, and carry different currents.
